## 6. Done Means

### Functional (testable by running the app)
- [ ] ED can log in and see program outcomes, fundraising revenue, and funder deadlines on one screen.
- [ ] ED can generate a Board Report for a selected period: shows all programs' outcomes, org-wide revenue summary, all funder deadlines, and an ED Notes field. Exports as PDF.
- [ ] ED or Head of Fundraising can generate a Funder Report for a selected funder and period: shows only that funder's linked programs' outcomes, revenue for that funder, and the funder's deadline. Exports as PDF.
- [ ] Both report types show "No data entered" for any metric with no entry in the selected period — never blank, never zero.
- [ ] A funder report cannot be exported if the selected funder has no linked programs — system blocks and prompts.
- [ ] Head of Fundraising can enter revenue actuals and set versioned revenue targets separately on `/revenue`. Actuals are editable and edits are logged with updated_by and updated_at. Setting a new target creates a new revenue_targets row without overwriting previous targets.
- [ ] Funder records show deadlines flagged by window: red (≤30 days), amber (31–60), yellow (61–90), none (>90).
- [ ] Off-track program metrics are flagged visually on the dashboard per their configured threshold.
- [ ] Revenue on-track/at-risk/off-track status is calculated using org-wide constants (80% / 60%), separate from per-metric thresholds.
- [ ] Staff users land directly on their program entry form and cannot navigate elsewhere.
- [ ] Admin can create programs, metrics (with targets and thresholds), and users. Deleting a metric with existing entries is blocked.
- [ ] All periods are anchored to the fiscal year January 1 – December 31. Annual metrics sum monthly entries from Jan 1 to Dec 31.
- [ ] Monthly metrics show "No data entered" in a report if no entry exists for that specific month.
- [ ] Annual metrics show the YTD actual if any entries exist for the fiscal year to date; show "No data entered" only if zero entries exist for the entire fiscal year to date.

### Behavioural (testable by living with it)
- [ ] ED prepares the next monthly board report using only this tool — no spreadsheet opened.
- [ ] No funder deadline is missed in the first 3 months of use.
- [ ] When a new grant opportunity arrives, the ED can pull a funder report the same day.

