## 11. Domain Rules

| Rule | Definition |
|---|---|
| **Program off-track flag** | A metric is flagged off-track when `actual_value < (target_value × off_track_threshold)`. Threshold is configured per metric by admin. Default: 0.80. |
| **Revenue target lookup** | For any funder/category and period, the applicable revenue target is the `revenue_targets` row with the latest `effective_from` date that is on or before the period start date, matching on funder_id and category. If no target exists, revenue cannot be given a status and the dashboard shows a configuration warning. |
| **Revenue status** | Revenue uses org-wide fixed constants, independent of per-metric thresholds. On-track: actual ≥ 80% of applicable target. At-risk: 60–79%. Off-track: below 60%. These constants are not user-configurable in v1. |
| **Deadline windows** | Due ≤30 days = red. 31–60 days = amber. 61–90 days = yellow. >90 days = no flag on dashboard. Calculated from today's date at page load. |
| **Missing data — monthly metrics** | A monthly metric shows "No data entered" in a report if no `metric_entries` row exists for that specific month. Never zero, never blank. |
| **Missing data — annual metrics** | An annual metric shows the YTD actual (sum of all monthly entries Jan 1 to end of selected period) if any entries exist for the fiscal year to date. Shows "No data entered" only if zero entries exist for the entire fiscal year to date. |
| **Fiscal year** | January 1 – December 31. All annual metric calculations aggregate monthly entries from Jan 1 to Dec 31 of the selected year. A report period of "June 2026" is month 6 of fiscal year 2026. |
| **Period storage** | All periods stored as the first day of the month (e.g. 2026-06-01). The UI may display as "June 2026" but the underlying value is always a date. |
| **Target lookup** | For any metric and period, the applicable target is the `metric_targets` row with the latest `effective_from` date that is on or before the period start date. If no target exists for a metric, it cannot be flagged as off-track and the dashboard shows a configuration warning. |
| **Annual vs. monthly targets** | Monthly metrics: compare actual for that month to the applicable target. Annual metrics: compare the YTD sum of all monthly entries (Jan–current month) to the applicable target, shown as progress-to-date. |
| **Funder report scope** | A funder report includes only programs linked via funder_programs. If no programs are linked, export is blocked. |
| **Board report deadline scope** | A board report shows all active funders and their next deadline date, sorted by proximity. Deadline window colouring (red/amber/yellow) applies. Funders with deadlines beyond 90 days are included but shown without a colour flag. This is intentional — the board should see the full funder calendar, not just what is imminent. |

