## 12. Build Order

Build in this sequence. Do not move to the next phase until the previous one passes its acceptance criteria.

### Phase 1 — Foundation & Admin
- Database schema (all tables in §9)
- User auth: login, session, role-based routing
- `/admin` with four sub-sections: Programs, Metrics, Users, Targets (see Flow D)

*Acceptance: Admin can create a program with 3 metrics (including off-track thresholds), set an initial target via metric_targets, create a staff user assigned to that program, create a Head of Fundraising user, and log in as each. Attempting to delete a metric blocks if entries exist. Updating a target creates a new metric_targets row without overwriting the previous one.*

### Phase 2 — Data Entry
- Staff entry form (`/programs/[id]/entry`) — staff see only their program
- Revenue entry screen (`/revenue`) — Head of Fundraising only
- Funder management (`/funders`, `/funders/[id]`) — ED and Head of Fundraising

*Acceptance: A staff user submits a monthly metric value and it appears in the database with correct period, metric_id, and entered_by. Head of Fundraising enters a revenue actual and sets a revenue target as separate operations. A funder record is created and linked to a program.*

### Phase 3 — Dashboard
- ED dashboard (`/dashboard`): program outcomes vs. targets, revenue status, funder deadline calendar
- Off-track flags and revenue status per domain rules (§11)
- Deadline window colouring per domain rules (§11)

*Acceptance: ED logs in and sees all three data domains with test data. Off-track metrics flagged correctly. Revenue status calculated using fixed constants. Funder deadlines colour-coded by window.*

### Phase 4 — Reporting
- `/report` screen: report type selector (board/funder), period selector, funder selector (funder report only), ED Notes field, export button
- Board report template: all active programs' outcomes, org-wide revenue summary, all funder deadlines, ED Notes
- Funder report template: linked programs' outcomes only, that funder's revenue, that funder's deadline, ED Notes
- "No data entered" shown for any metric with no entry in the period
- Export blocked if funder report selected with no linked programs

*Acceptance: ED generates a board report for a test period. ED and Head of Fundraising each generate a funder report. All export as clean PDF. A period with missing data shows "No data entered." A funder with no linked programs cannot be exported — system shows a prompt.*

